<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Plants always twining. Longest leaf segments on mature branches &lt;4 cm long; sepals narrowly elliptic 5-9 mm; corolla 1.5-2.8 cm long. The basal cylindrical part of the corolla tube is usually &lt;5 mm long but in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="ternifolia" variety="valida">
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is only known from the type locality in Colima, the basal cylindrical tube is 16-18 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
